Measurement of the 11C-flumazenil binding in the visual cortex predicts the prognosis of hemianopia. In order to determine whether functional neuroimaging studies can predict the prognosis of hemianopia due to organic cerebral disorders, we studied 8 patients (6 men and 2 women age, 56.0+/-8.6 years) with homonymous hemianopia and compared them with 15 normal subjects (6 men and 9 women